{"type":"message","id":"ff3c003f","parentId":"4b0d030c","timestamp":"2026-03-03T07:34:25.005Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"这是QVeris API的一个bug或者工具定义问题。参数没有被正确传递。让我查看是否有其他方式来使用这个工具，或者查看documentation。\n\n让我尝试一个最简单的FMP新闻API。","thinkingSignature":"95f2fad9dc0838e8e406813fb6dfd82e4696170388d48fc4329dc3690c9b841c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8i1r3z2y2f84_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && node -e \"\nconst API_KEY = process.env.QVERIS_API_KEY;\nconst API_BASE = 'https://qveris.ai/api/v1';\n\nasync function execute() {\n  const res = await fetch(\\`\\${API_BASE}/tools/execute\\`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      'Authorization': \\`Bearer \\${API_KEY}\\`\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ \n      tool_id: 'financial_modeling_prep.fmp_articles.list.v1.2df51706', \n      params: { limit: '20', page: '0' }\n    })\n  });\n  const data = await res.json();\n  console.log(JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n}\nexecute();\n\"","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":24623,"output":242,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38849,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772523259103}}
{"type":"message","id":"38b4bacd","parentId":"ff3c003f","timestamp":"2026-03-03T07:34:28.537Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8i1r3z2y2f84_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"f339cfb3-ea2f-49b7-a404-ba6f3a7ee71e\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (55149 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260303%2Ffinancial_modeling_prep.fmp_articles.list.v1.2df51706%2F63411a13fb81412a8ba2c0f49808c10b.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772530467&Signature=gwiqisgelZpvfJ%2FnNkhc9hvxZfk%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"[{\\\"title\\\": \\\"SoFi Technologies: A Fintech Leader's Strategic Moves and Market Position\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:05:53\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li><strong>Noto Anthony's insider purchase</strong> of 56,000 shares signals confidence in SoFi Technologies (NASDAQ:SOFI), potentially influencing investor sentiment.</li>\\\\n<li>The company's <strong>positive upgrade from Wall Street</strong> and subsequent 3.32% stock price increase reflect optimism about its future prospects amidst competitive fintech landscape.</li>\\\\n<li>SoFi's <strong>financial metrics</strong>, including a P/E ratio of <strong>46.72</strong> and a debt-to-equity ratio of <strong>0.17</strong>, highlight its market valuation and conservative debt approach, despite challenges in cash flow generation.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n\\\\n<p>SoFi Technologies, trading under the symbol <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/SOFI\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:SOFI</a>, is a prominent player in the fintech industry, offering a range of financial services including loans, banking, and investment products. The company competes with other fintech firms like Robinhood and Square. Recently, the CEO, Noto Anthony, made a significant purchase of 56,000 shares at $17.88 each, increasing his total ownership to 11,675,452 shares.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>This insider purchase by Noto Anthony comes at a time when SoFi has received a positive upgrade from Wall Street, following a steep sell-off. The stock price increased by <strong>3.32%</strong>, reflecting a positive market sentiment. This suggests that investors are optimistic about the company's future prospects, especially given its impressive revenue and member growth.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>SoFi's financial metrics provide further insight into its market position. The company has a price-to-earnings (P/E) ratio of <strong>46.72</strong>, indicating that investors are willing to pay a premium for its earnings. The price-to-sales ratio of <strong>4.92</strong> and enterprise value to sales ratio of <strong>4.26</strong> suggest that the market values SoFi's sales highly. However, the negative enterprise value to operating cash flow ratio of <strong>-8.60</strong> highlights potential challenges in generating cash flow from operations.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Despite these challenges, SoFi's earnings yield of <strong>2.14%</strong> offers a glimpse into the earnings generated per dollar invested. Additionally, the company's debt-to-equity ratio of <strong>0.17</strong> indicates a conservative approach to debt, which could be advantageous in maintaining financial stability. As highlighted by the recent Wall Street upgrade, if sentiment continues to improve and earnings rise, SoFi could see further upside potential.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:SOFI\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5ffd18d64d83712229904.jpeg\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/sofi-technologies-strategic-moves-market-position\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Danny Green\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Webtoon Entertainment's Upcoming Earnings Report: A Detailed Analysis\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:00:07\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>Webtoon Entertainment (<a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/WBTN\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:WBTN</a>) anticipates an EPS loss of <strong>$0.04</strong>, marking a 33.3% decline year-over-year.</li>\\\\n<li>Revenue projections stand at approximately <strong>$337.2 million</strong>, a 5.2% decrease from the previous year, yet slightly above analyst expectations.</li>\\\\n<li>The company showcases a strong liquidity position with a current ratio of <strong>2.52</strong> and a low debt-to-equity ratio of <strong>0.018</strong>, despite challenges in generating cash flow from operations.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Webtoon Entertainment (<a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/WBTN\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:WBTN</a>) is a leading digital content company known for its innovative web-based comics and storytelling platforms. As the company gears up to release its quarterly earnings on March 3, 2026, Wall Street sets its sights on an earnings per share (EPS) loss of <strong>$0.04</strong>. This forecasted figure represents a significant 33.3% decline from the same period last year, underscoring the ongoing financial hurdles Webtoon Entertainment faces.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Despite these challenges, revenue projections for WBTN are pegged at approximately <strong>$337.2 million</strong>, slightly surpassing the $334 million anticipated by analysts. This revenue estimate indicates a 5.2% year-over-year decrease, pointing to a dip in sales performance. Nevertheless, the consensus EPS estimate has remained steady over the past 30 days, suggesting that analysts maintain confidence in their initial projections.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Examining WBTN's financial metrics unveils a complex scenario. The company's negative price-to-earnings (P/E) ratio of <strong>-11.28</strong> mirrors its current losses, while a price-to-sales ratio of <strong>1.08</strong> indicates that investors are paying $1.08 for every dollar of sales, a figure that is considered relatively reasonable. Moreover, the enterprise value to sales ratio of <strong>0.68</strong> might signal that the company is undervalued in terms of its sales.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Despite the financial challenges, Webtoon Entertainment boasts a robust liquidity position, evidenced by a current ratio of <strong>2.52</strong>. This ratio highlights the company's capability to cover short-term liabilities. Additionally, a low debt-to-equity ratio of <strong>0.018</strong> demonstrates minimal reliance on debt financing. However, the significantly negative enterprise value to operating cash flow ratio of <strong>-189.25</strong> raises concerns about the company's ability to generate cash flow from its operations.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:WBTN\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5ff648d64d8371222974b.png\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/webtoon-entertainment-earnings-report-analysis-march-2026\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Andrew Wynn\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Pacira BioSciences, Inc. (NASDAQ:PCRX) Financial Performance and Competitive Landscape\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:00:03\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li><strong>Pacira BioSciences, Inc. (NASDAQ:PCRX)</strong> has a <strong>Return on Invested Capital (ROIC) of 1.74%</strong>, which is below its Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) of <strong>6.19%</strong>, indicating inefficiencies in capital utilization.</li>\\\\n<li><strong>PTC Therapeutics</strong> showcases a high ROIC of <strong>37.39%</strong> against a WACC of <strong>7.70%</strong>, leading to a ROIC to WACC ratio of <strong>4.86</strong>, highlighting strong capital efficiency.</li>\\\\n<li>Comparatively, <strong>Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical</strong> and <strong>Enanta Pharmaceuticals</strong> report negative ROICs, suggesting challenges in generating sufficient returns on their capital.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n<p><a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/PCRX\\\\\\\">Pacira BioSciences, Inc. (NASDAQ:PCRX)</a> is a pharmaceutical company that focuses on developing and commercializing non-opioid pain management and regenerative health solutions. The company's flagship product, EXPAREL, is used for postsurgical pain management. In the competitive landscape, Pacira faces peers like Supernus Pharmaceuticals, PTC Therapeutics, Ironwood Pharmaceuticals, Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical, and Enanta Pharmaceuticals.</p>\\\\n<p>In evaluating Pacira's financial performance, the <strong>Return on Invested Capital (ROIC)</strong> is a crucial metric. Pacira's ROIC stands at <strong>1.74%</strong>, which is significantly lower than its <strong>Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC)</strong> of <strong>6.19%</strong>. This indicates that the company is not generating returns that exceed its cost of capital, suggesting inefficiencies in capital utilization.</p>\\\\n<p>Comparatively, Supernus Pharmaceuticals has a negative ROIC of <strong>-0.31%</strong> against a WACC of <strong>3.02%</strong>.<strong> </strong>This shows that Supernus is also struggling to generate returns above its cost of capital. On the other hand, PTC Therapeutics shines with a ROIC of <strong>37.39%</strong> and a WACC of <strong>7.70%</strong>, leading to a ROIC to WACC ratio of <strong>4.86</strong>, indicating strong capital efficiency.</p>\\\\n<p>Ironwood Pharmaceuticals also demonstrates effective capital use with a ROIC of <strong>21.34%</strong> and a WACC of <strong>5.68%</strong>, resulting in a ROIC to WACC ratio of <strong>3.76</strong>. In contrast, Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical and Enanta Pharmaceuticals have negative ROICs of <strong>-43.59%</strong> and <strong>-22.45%</strong>, respectively, with ROIC to WACC ratios of <strong>-9.48</strong> and <strong>-3.53</strong>, indicating challenges in generating sufficient returns on their capital.</p>\\\\n<p>Among its peers, PTC Therapeutics stands out with the highest ROIC to WACC ratio, suggesting it is effectively using its capital to generate returns well above its cost. This positions PTC Therapeutics as a leader in capital efficiency, while Pacira BioSciences and others may need to reassess their capital strategies to improve financial performance.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:PCRX\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5ff2c8d64d837122295cd.png\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/pacira-biosciences-pcrx-financial-performance-competitive-landscape\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Rayan Ahmad\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Amylyx Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMLX) Sees Rising Optimism Among Analysts\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:00:02\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>The consensus price target for <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/AMLX\\\\\\\">Amylyx Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMLX)</a> has increased from $19.14 to $23.50, indicating growing analyst optimism.</li>\\\\n<li>Significant interest from major financial institutions during the recent earnings call highlights the potential impact of Amylyx's clinical trials and strategic partnerships on its market performance.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n<p><strong>Amylyx Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMLX)</strong> is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company dedicated to developing treatments for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) and other neurodegenerative diseases. Their main product in development, AMX0035, is a dual UPR-Bax apoptosis inhibitor. This innovative treatment combines sodium phenylbutyrate and taurursodiol, aiming to address the unmet needs in ALS treatment.</p>\\\\n<p>The consensus price target for Amylyx has seen a notable increase over the past year, rising from <strong>$19.14</strong> to <strong>$23.50</strong>. This upward trend indicates growing optimism among analysts about the company's future. The increase could be linked to advancements in their product pipeline or positive clinical trial results, as highlighted by the recent Q3 2025 earnings call attended by key company figures and analysts from major financial institutions.</p>\\\\n<p>Wall Street analysts project a <strong>29.3%</strong> upside for the stock. This suggests a strong consensus among analysts in raising earnings estimates, indicating potential growth for Amylyx. The company's recent earnings call featured participation from prominent analysts, including those from Guggenheim Securities, TD Cowen, and Goldman Sachs Group. This level of interest from major financial institutions underscores the significance of Amylyx's developments and the potential impact of their clinical trials, regulatory progress, and strategic partnerships on the stock's performance.</p>\\\\n<p>Investors should keep an eye on <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/AMLX\\\\\\\">Amylyx Pharmaceuticals</a> for updates on their clinical trials and regulatory progress. These factors, along with potential new partnerships or collaborations, could further influence the stock's target price and overall market performance. The biopharmaceutical sector's growing interest in neurodegenerative diseases may also play a role in shaping the company's future prospects.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:AMLX\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5feb38d64d837122293be.png\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/amylyx-pharmaceuticals-analyst-optimism-rising\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Andrew Wynn\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Civeo Corporation (NYSE: CVEO) Financial Overview and Analyst Insights\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:00:01\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>The stock consensus target price for <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/CVEO\\\\\\\">Civeo Corporation (NYSE:CVEO)</a> remains stable at <strong>$33</strong>, indicating a positive shift in analyst sentiment.</li>\\\\n<li>Civeo's Australian segment is a key growth driver, with a revenue target of AUD 500 million by 2027, while its Canadian operations see margin expansion.</li>\\\\n<li>The company's recent Q3 2025 earnings report shows a revenue of <strong>$170.5 million</strong> and an adjusted EBITDA of <strong>$28.8 million</strong>, underscoring its strong financial performance and growth potential.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Civeo Corporation (NYSE: CVEO) is a key player in the hospitality services sector, specifically catering to the natural resource industry. The company operates across Canada, Australia, and the United States, providing essential services such as developing lodges and villages, mobile accommodations, and support services like food, housekeeping, and maintenance. Their primary clientele includes sectors like oil, mining, engineering, and oilfield and mining services.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>The stock consensus target price for <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/CVEO\\\\\\\">Civeo</a> has shown stability over the past month and quarter, maintaining an average price target of <strong>$33</strong>. This consistency suggests that analysts have a steady outlook on the stock in the short term. However, the increase from last year's average price target of $30.5 to $33 indicates a positive shift in analyst sentiment over the past year.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Civeo is set to hold its fourth quarter 2025 earnings conference call on March 3rd, where it will discuss its financial and operating results. Analyst Stephen Gengaro from Stifel Nicolaus has set a price target of $28 for the stock, suggesting potential for upward movement. The company is anticipated to surpass earnings estimates, as highlighted by Zacks, which could further influence analyst price targets.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Civeo's Australian segment is a significant growth driver, focusing on integrated, asset-light services with a target to achieve AUD 500 million in revenue by 2027. Meanwhile, the Canadian operations are experiencing margin expansion despite declining revenues. The company is actively engaging in a share buyback program, allocating nearly all of its free cash flow to buybacks, amounting to $52 million year-to-date, enhancing equity value for shareholders.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Civeo's recent Q3 2025 earnings call provided insights into its financial performance and strategic direction. The company reported a revenue of <strong>$170.5 million</strong> and an adjusted EBITDA of <strong>$28.8 million</strong>. Analysts, including Stephen Gengaro, have set a price target of $28, indicating a positive outlook for the company's financial performance. The company's strong earnings acceleration and projected EPS growth make it a compelling investment opportunity.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NYSE:CVEO\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5fd4d8d64d83712228b10.png\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/civeo-corporation-financial-overview-analyst-insights\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Alex Lavoie\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"UroGen Pharma Ltd. (NASDAQ:URGN) Performance and Strategic Initiatives\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 20:05:50\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>UroGen Pharma Ltd. (<a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/URGN\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:URGN</a>) reported a quarterly loss of <strong>$0.54 per share</strong>, outperforming the Zacks Consensus Estimate.</li>\\\\n<li>The company achieved <strong>$37.84 million</strong> in revenue for Q4 2025, surpassing expectations and marking significant year-over-year growth.</li>\\\\n<li>Strategic initiatives include the commercial launch of ZUSDURI&trade;, with net sales of <strong>$15.8 million</strong> in 2025, and a favorable refinancing agreement with Pharmakon Advisors.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n<p>UroGen Pharma Ltd. (<a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/URGN\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:URGN</a>) is a biopharmaceutical company focused on developing and commercializing innovative solutions for urological and uro-oncological diseases. The company is part of the Zacks Medical - Biomedical and Genetics industry. UroGen's key products include ZUSDURI&trade;, the first FDA-approved treatment for recurrent low-grade intermediate-risk non-muscle invasive bladder cancer, and JELMYTO&reg;, which has shown a 7% year-over-year growth in demand.</p>\\\\n<p>On March 2, 2026, Oppenheimer reiterated its \\\\\\\"Outperform\\\\\\\" rating for UroGen Pharma, maintaining its previous grade. At the time, the stock was trading at $19.93. Despite a recent decrease of 8.06%, with the stock priced at $19.95, UroGen's performance has shown resilience. The stock has fluctuated between $18.18 and $21.69 today, with a market capitalization of approximately $933.8 million.</p>\\\\n<p>UroGen Pharma's Q4 2025 earnings call, provided insights into the company's financial performance. The company reported a quarterly loss of <strong>$0.54 per share</strong>, better than the Zacks Consensus Estimate of a <strong>$0.66 loss</strong>. This marks an improvement from the <strong>$0.80 per share loss</strong> reported in the same quarter last year, representing an <strong>18.18%</strong> positive earnings surprise.</p>\\\\n<p>In terms of revenue, UroGen Pharma achieved <strong>$37.84 million</strong> for the quarter ending December 2025, surpassing the Zacks Consensus Estimate by <strong>6.42%</strong>. This is a significant increase from the <strong>$24.57 million</strong> in revenue reported in the same quarter the previous year. However, the company has only exceeded consensus revenue estimates once in the last four quarters.</p>\\\\n<p>UroGen Pharma's strategic initiatives include the commercial launch of ZUSDURI&trade;, with net sales of <strong>$15.8 million</strong> in 2025. The permanent J Code for ZUSDURI, effective January 1, 2026, is expected to streamline reimbursement procedures and enhance patient access. Additionally, UroGen has refinanced its existing term loan with Pharmakon Advisors, securing additional non-dilutive capital under more favorable terms.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:URGN\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5f3de8d64d837122251a7.jpeg\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/urogen-pharma-ltd-urgn-q4-2025-earnings-strategic-growth-initiatives\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Alex Lavoie\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Insider Transactions and Financial Health of Viavi Solutions Inc. (NASDAQ:VIAV)\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 20:00:05\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>Executive insider transactions at <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/VIAV\\\\\\\">Viavi Solutions Inc. (NASDAQ:VIAV)</a> may signal internal sentiment towards the company's future performance.</li>\\\\n<li>Despite negative earnings, Viavi's valuation metrics like the price-to-sales ratio indicate investor confidence in its revenue potential.</li>\\\\n<li>The company's financial health is underscored by a strong current ratio, though its use of debt is notable.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n\\\\n<p><a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/VIAV\\\\\\\">Viavi Solutions Inc. (NASDAQ:VIAV)</a> is a prominent player in the network testing and security industry. The company is known for its innovative solutions that help ensure the reliability and security of networks. Viavi competes with other tech firms in the network solutions space, striving to maintain its leadership position through strategic decisions and market activities.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>On March 2, 2026, McNab Paul, the Executive Vice President, Chief Marketing & Strategy Officer of Viavi, sold 3,551 shares of the company's common stock at $32.89 each.\",\n    \"content_schema\": {\n      \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"title\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"date\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"content\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"tickers\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"image\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"link\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"author\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"site\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"author\",\n          \"content\",\n          \"date\",\n          \"image\",\n          \"link\",\n          \"site\",\n          \"tickers\",\n          \"title\"\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 1910.02,\n  \"cost\": 6.5\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3527,"aggregated":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"f339cfb3-ea2f-49b7-a404-ba6f3a7ee71e\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (55149 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260303%2Ffinancial_modeling_prep.fmp_articles.list.v1.2df51706%2F63411a13fb81412a8ba2c0f49808c10b.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772530467&Signature=gwiqisgelZpvfJ%2FnNkhc9hvxZfk%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"[{\\\"title\\\": \\\"SoFi Technologies: A Fintech Leader's Strategic Moves and Market Position\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:05:53\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li><strong>Noto Anthony's insider purchase</strong> of 56,000 shares signals confidence in SoFi Technologies (NASDAQ:SOFI), potentially influencing investor sentiment.</li>\\\\n<li>The company's <strong>positive upgrade from Wall Street</strong> and subsequent 3.32% stock price increase reflect optimism about its future prospects amidst competitive fintech landscape.</li>\\\\n<li>SoFi's <strong>financial metrics</strong>, including a P/E ratio of <strong>46.72</strong> and a debt-to-equity ratio of <strong>0.17</strong>, highlight its market valuation and conservative debt approach, despite challenges in cash flow generation.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n\\\\n<p>SoFi Technologies, trading under the symbol <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/SOFI\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:SOFI</a>, is a prominent player in the fintech industry, offering a range of financial services including loans, banking, and investment products. The company competes with other fintech firms like Robinhood and Square. Recently, the CEO, Noto Anthony, made a significant purchase of 56,000 shares at $17.88 each, increasing his total ownership to 11,675,452 shares.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>This insider purchase by Noto Anthony comes at a time when SoFi has received a positive upgrade from Wall Street, following a steep sell-off. The stock price increased by <strong>3.32%</strong>, reflecting a positive market sentiment. This suggests that investors are optimistic about the company's future prospects, especially given its impressive revenue and member growth.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>SoFi's financial metrics provide further insight into its market position. The company has a price-to-earnings (P/E) ratio of <strong>46.72</strong>, indicating that investors are willing to pay a premium for its earnings. The price-to-sales ratio of <strong>4.92</strong> and enterprise value to sales ratio of <strong>4.26</strong> suggest that the market values SoFi's sales highly. However, the negative enterprise value to operating cash flow ratio of <strong>-8.60</strong> highlights potential challenges in generating cash flow from operations.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Despite these challenges, SoFi's earnings yield of <strong>2.14%</strong> offers a glimpse into the earnings generated per dollar invested. Additionally, the company's debt-to-equity ratio of <strong>0.17</strong> indicates a conservative approach to debt, which could be advantageous in maintaining financial stability. As highlighted by the recent Wall Street upgrade, if sentiment continues to improve and earnings rise, SoFi could see further upside potential.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:SOFI\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5ffd18d64d83712229904.jpeg\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/sofi-technologies-strategic-moves-market-position\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Danny Green\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Webtoon Entertainment's Upcoming Earnings Report: A Detailed Analysis\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:00:07\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>Webtoon Entertainment (<a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/WBTN\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:WBTN</a>) anticipates an EPS loss of <strong>$0.04</strong>, marking a 33.3% decline year-over-year.</li>\\\\n<li>Revenue projections stand at approximately <strong>$337.2 million</strong>, a 5.2% decrease from the previous year, yet slightly above analyst expectations.</li>\\\\n<li>The company showcases a strong liquidity position with a current ratio of <strong>2.52</strong> and a low debt-to-equity ratio of <strong>0.018</strong>, despite challenges in generating cash flow from operations.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Webtoon Entertainment (<a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/WBTN\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:WBTN</a>) is a leading digital content company known for its innovative web-based comics and storytelling platforms. As the company gears up to release its quarterly earnings on March 3, 2026, Wall Street sets its sights on an earnings per share (EPS) loss of <strong>$0.04</strong>. This forecasted figure represents a significant 33.3% decline from the same period last year, underscoring the ongoing financial hurdles Webtoon Entertainment faces.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Despite these challenges, revenue projections for WBTN are pegged at approximately <strong>$337.2 million</strong>, slightly surpassing the $334 million anticipated by analysts. This revenue estimate indicates a 5.2% year-over-year decrease, pointing to a dip in sales performance. Nevertheless, the consensus EPS estimate has remained steady over the past 30 days, suggesting that analysts maintain confidence in their initial projections.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Examining WBTN's financial metrics unveils a complex scenario. The company's negative price-to-earnings (P/E) ratio of <strong>-11.28</strong> mirrors its current losses, while a price-to-sales ratio of <strong>1.08</strong> indicates that investors are paying $1.08 for every dollar of sales, a figure that is considered relatively reasonable. Moreover, the enterprise value to sales ratio of <strong>0.68</strong> might signal that the company is undervalued in terms of its sales.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Despite the financial challenges, Webtoon Entertainment boasts a robust liquidity position, evidenced by a current ratio of <strong>2.52</strong>. This ratio highlights the company's capability to cover short-term liabilities. Additionally, a low debt-to-equity ratio of <strong>0.018</strong> demonstrates minimal reliance on debt financing. However, the significantly negative enterprise value to operating cash flow ratio of <strong>-189.25</strong> raises concerns about the company's ability to generate cash flow from its operations.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:WBTN\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5ff648d64d8371222974b.png\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/webtoon-entertainment-earnings-report-analysis-march-2026\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Andrew Wynn\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Pacira BioSciences, Inc. (NASDAQ:PCRX) Financial Performance and Competitive Landscape\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:00:03\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li><strong>Pacira BioSciences, Inc. (NASDAQ:PCRX)</strong> has a <strong>Return on Invested Capital (ROIC) of 1.74%</strong>, which is below its Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) of <strong>6.19%</strong>, indicating inefficiencies in capital utilization.</li>\\\\n<li><strong>PTC Therapeutics</strong> showcases a high ROIC of <strong>37.39%</strong> against a WACC of <strong>7.70%</strong>, leading to a ROIC to WACC ratio of <strong>4.86</strong>, highlighting strong capital efficiency.</li>\\\\n<li>Comparatively, <strong>Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical</strong> and <strong>Enanta Pharmaceuticals</strong> report negative ROICs, suggesting challenges in generating sufficient returns on their capital.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n<p><a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/PCRX\\\\\\\">Pacira BioSciences, Inc. (NASDAQ:PCRX)</a> is a pharmaceutical company that focuses on developing and commercializing non-opioid pain management and regenerative health solutions. The company's flagship product, EXPAREL, is used for postsurgical pain management. In the competitive landscape, Pacira faces peers like Supernus Pharmaceuticals, PTC Therapeutics, Ironwood Pharmaceuticals, Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical, and Enanta Pharmaceuticals.</p>\\\\n<p>In evaluating Pacira's financial performance, the <strong>Return on Invested Capital (ROIC)</strong> is a crucial metric. Pacira's ROIC stands at <strong>1.74%</strong>, which is significantly lower than its <strong>Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC)</strong> of <strong>6.19%</strong>. This indicates that the company is not generating returns that exceed its cost of capital, suggesting inefficiencies in capital utilization.</p>\\\\n<p>Comparatively, Supernus Pharmaceuticals has a negative ROIC of <strong>-0.31%</strong> against a WACC of <strong>3.02%</strong>.<strong> </strong>This shows that Supernus is also struggling to generate returns above its cost of capital. On the other hand, PTC Therapeutics shines with a ROIC of <strong>37.39%</strong> and a WACC of <strong>7.70%</strong>, leading to a ROIC to WACC ratio of <strong>4.86</strong>, indicating strong capital efficiency.</p>\\\\n<p>Ironwood Pharmaceuticals also demonstrates effective capital use with a ROIC of <strong>21.34%</strong> and a WACC of <strong>5.68%</strong>, resulting in a ROIC to WACC ratio of <strong>3.76</strong>. In contrast, Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical and Enanta Pharmaceuticals have negative ROICs of <strong>-43.59%</strong> and <strong>-22.45%</strong>, respectively, with ROIC to WACC ratios of <strong>-9.48</strong> and <strong>-3.53</strong>, indicating challenges in generating sufficient returns on their capital.</p>\\\\n<p>Among its peers, PTC Therapeutics stands out with the highest ROIC to WACC ratio, suggesting it is effectively using its capital to generate returns well above its cost. This positions PTC Therapeutics as a leader in capital efficiency, while Pacira BioSciences and others may need to reassess their capital strategies to improve financial performance.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:PCRX\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5ff2c8d64d837122295cd.png\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/pacira-biosciences-pcrx-financial-performance-competitive-landscape\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Rayan Ahmad\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Amylyx Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMLX) Sees Rising Optimism Among Analysts\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:00:02\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>The consensus price target for <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/AMLX\\\\\\\">Amylyx Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMLX)</a> has increased from $19.14 to $23.50, indicating growing analyst optimism.</li>\\\\n<li>Significant interest from major financial institutions during the recent earnings call highlights the potential impact of Amylyx's clinical trials and strategic partnerships on its market performance.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n<p><strong>Amylyx Pharmaceuticals, Inc. (NASDAQ:AMLX)</strong> is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company dedicated to developing treatments for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) and other neurodegenerative diseases. Their main product in development, AMX0035, is a dual UPR-Bax apoptosis inhibitor. This innovative treatment combines sodium phenylbutyrate and taurursodiol, aiming to address the unmet needs in ALS treatment.</p>\\\\n<p>The consensus price target for Amylyx has seen a notable increase over the past year, rising from <strong>$19.14</strong> to <strong>$23.50</strong>. This upward trend indicates growing optimism among analysts about the company's future. The increase could be linked to advancements in their product pipeline or positive clinical trial results, as highlighted by the recent Q3 2025 earnings call attended by key company figures and analysts from major financial institutions.</p>\\\\n<p>Wall Street analysts project a <strong>29.3%</strong> upside for the stock. This suggests a strong consensus among analysts in raising earnings estimates, indicating potential growth for Amylyx. The company's recent earnings call featured participation from prominent analysts, including those from Guggenheim Securities, TD Cowen, and Goldman Sachs Group. This level of interest from major financial institutions underscores the significance of Amylyx's developments and the potential impact of their clinical trials, regulatory progress, and strategic partnerships on the stock's performance.</p>\\\\n<p>Investors should keep an eye on <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/AMLX\\\\\\\">Amylyx Pharmaceuticals</a> for updates on their clinical trials and regulatory progress. These factors, along with potential new partnerships or collaborations, could further influence the stock's target price and overall market performance. The biopharmaceutical sector's growing interest in neurodegenerative diseases may also play a role in shaping the company's future prospects.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:AMLX\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5feb38d64d837122293be.png\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/amylyx-pharmaceuticals-analyst-optimism-rising\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Andrew Wynn\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Civeo Corporation (NYSE: CVEO) Financial Overview and Analyst Insights\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 21:00:01\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>The stock consensus target price for <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/CVEO\\\\\\\">Civeo Corporation (NYSE:CVEO)</a> remains stable at <strong>$33</strong>, indicating a positive shift in analyst sentiment.</li>\\\\n<li>Civeo's Australian segment is a key growth driver, with a revenue target of AUD 500 million by 2027, while its Canadian operations see margin expansion.</li>\\\\n<li>The company's recent Q3 2025 earnings report shows a revenue of <strong>$170.5 million</strong> and an adjusted EBITDA of <strong>$28.8 million</strong>, underscoring its strong financial performance and growth potential.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Civeo Corporation (NYSE: CVEO) is a key player in the hospitality services sector, specifically catering to the natural resource industry. The company operates across Canada, Australia, and the United States, providing essential services such as developing lodges and villages, mobile accommodations, and support services like food, housekeeping, and maintenance. Their primary clientele includes sectors like oil, mining, engineering, and oilfield and mining services.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>The stock consensus target price for <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/CVEO\\\\\\\">Civeo</a> has shown stability over the past month and quarter, maintaining an average price target of <strong>$33</strong>. This consistency suggests that analysts have a steady outlook on the stock in the short term. However, the increase from last year's average price target of $30.5 to $33 indicates a positive shift in analyst sentiment over the past year.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Civeo is set to hold its fourth quarter 2025 earnings conference call on March 3rd, where it will discuss its financial and operating results. Analyst Stephen Gengaro from Stifel Nicolaus has set a price target of $28 for the stock, suggesting potential for upward movement. The company is anticipated to surpass earnings estimates, as highlighted by Zacks, which could further influence analyst price targets.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Civeo's Australian segment is a significant growth driver, focusing on integrated, asset-light services with a target to achieve AUD 500 million in revenue by 2027. Meanwhile, the Canadian operations are experiencing margin expansion despite declining revenues. The company is actively engaging in a share buyback program, allocating nearly all of its free cash flow to buybacks, amounting to $52 million year-to-date, enhancing equity value for shareholders.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>Civeo's recent Q3 2025 earnings call provided insights into its financial performance and strategic direction. The company reported a revenue of <strong>$170.5 million</strong> and an adjusted EBITDA of <strong>$28.8 million</strong>. Analysts, including Stephen Gengaro, have set a price target of $28, indicating a positive outlook for the company's financial performance. The company's strong earnings acceleration and projected EPS growth make it a compelling investment opportunity.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NYSE:CVEO\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5fd4d8d64d83712228b10.png\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/civeo-corporation-financial-overview-analyst-insights\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Alex Lavoie\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"UroGen Pharma Ltd. (NASDAQ:URGN) Performance and Strategic Initiatives\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 20:05:50\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>UroGen Pharma Ltd. (<a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/URGN\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:URGN</a>) reported a quarterly loss of <strong>$0.54 per share</strong>, outperforming the Zacks Consensus Estimate.</li>\\\\n<li>The company achieved <strong>$37.84 million</strong> in revenue for Q4 2025, surpassing expectations and marking significant year-over-year growth.</li>\\\\n<li>Strategic initiatives include the commercial launch of ZUSDURI&trade;, with net sales of <strong>$15.8 million</strong> in 2025, and a favorable refinancing agreement with Pharmakon Advisors.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n<p>UroGen Pharma Ltd. (<a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/URGN\\\\\\\">NASDAQ:URGN</a>) is a biopharmaceutical company focused on developing and commercializing innovative solutions for urological and uro-oncological diseases. The company is part of the Zacks Medical - Biomedical and Genetics industry. UroGen's key products include ZUSDURI&trade;, the first FDA-approved treatment for recurrent low-grade intermediate-risk non-muscle invasive bladder cancer, and JELMYTO&reg;, which has shown a 7% year-over-year growth in demand.</p>\\\\n<p>On March 2, 2026, Oppenheimer reiterated its \\\\\\\"Outperform\\\\\\\" rating for UroGen Pharma, maintaining its previous grade. At the time, the stock was trading at $19.93. Despite a recent decrease of 8.06%, with the stock priced at $19.95, UroGen's performance has shown resilience. The stock has fluctuated between $18.18 and $21.69 today, with a market capitalization of approximately $933.8 million.</p>\\\\n<p>UroGen Pharma's Q4 2025 earnings call, provided insights into the company's financial performance. The company reported a quarterly loss of <strong>$0.54 per share</strong>, better than the Zacks Consensus Estimate of a <strong>$0.66 loss</strong>. This marks an improvement from the <strong>$0.80 per share loss</strong> reported in the same quarter last year, representing an <strong>18.18%</strong> positive earnings surprise.</p>\\\\n<p>In terms of revenue, UroGen Pharma achieved <strong>$37.84 million</strong> for the quarter ending December 2025, surpassing the Zacks Consensus Estimate by <strong>6.42%</strong>. This is a significant increase from the <strong>$24.57 million</strong> in revenue reported in the same quarter the previous year. However, the company has only exceeded consensus revenue estimates once in the last four quarters.</p>\\\\n<p>UroGen Pharma's strategic initiatives include the commercial launch of ZUSDURI&trade;, with net sales of <strong>$15.8 million</strong> in 2025. The permanent J Code for ZUSDURI, effective January 1, 2026, is expected to streamline reimbursement procedures and enhance patient access. Additionally, UroGen has refinanced its existing term loan with Pharmakon Advisors, securing additional non-dilutive capital under more favorable terms.</p>\\\", \\\"tickers\\\": \\\"NASDAQ:URGN\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://portal.financialmodelingprep.com/positions/69a5f3de8d64d837122251a7.jpeg\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/urogen-pharma-ltd-urgn-q4-2025-earnings-strategic-growth-initiatives\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"Alex Lavoie\\\", \\\"site\\\": \\\"Financial Modeling Prep\\\"}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Insider Transactions and Financial Health of Viavi Solutions Inc. (NASDAQ:VIAV)\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-02 20:00:05\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"<ul>\\\\n<li>Executive insider transactions at <a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/VIAV\\\\\\\">Viavi Solutions Inc. (NASDAQ:VIAV)</a> may signal internal sentiment towards the company's future performance.</li>\\\\n<li>Despite negative earnings, Viavi's valuation metrics like the price-to-sales ratio indicate investor confidence in its revenue potential.</li>\\\\n<li>The company's financial health is underscored by a strong current ratio, though its use of debt is notable.</li>\\\\n</ul>\\\\n\\\\n<p><a href=\\\\\\\"https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/financial-summary/VIAV\\\\\\\">Viavi Solutions Inc. (NASDAQ:VIAV)</a> is a prominent player in the network testing and security industry. The company is known for its innovative solutions that help ensure the reliability and security of networks. Viavi competes with other tech firms in the network solutions space, striving to maintain its leadership position through strategic decisions and market activities.</p>\\\\n\\\\n<p>On March 2, 2026, McNab Paul, the Executive Vice President, Chief Marketing & Strategy Officer of Viavi, sold 3,551 shares of the company's common stock at $32.89 each.\",\n    \"content_schema\": {\n      \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"title\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"date\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"content\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"tickers\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"image\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"link\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"author\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"site\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"author\",\n          \"content\",\n          \"date\",\n          \"image\",\n          \"link\",\n          \"site\",\n          \"tickers\",\n          \"title\"\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 1910.02,\n  \"cost\": 6.5\n}","cwd":"/Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772523268535}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3f0ae1c","parentId":"38b4bacd","timestamp":"2026-03-03T07:34:33.844Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"好的，FMP API可以工作！但是用户明确要求使用finnhub。让我检查finnhub的问题。\n\n但首先，我需要看一下finnhub是否返回类似于\"热度\"的字段。让我再尝试一下finnhub工具，使用不同的方式调用。\n\n让我先检查一下finnhub API的原始参数是否正确。","thinkingSignature":"60b66746d6b8ce307f21e68e19a5cbc78bed1f4b6d89d20f2b7e826f8401d174"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x160cb9zefcm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://finnhub.io/api/v1/news?category=general&token=demo\" | head -c 2000","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":30281,"output":130,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44395,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772523268538}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b760bd5","parentId":"f3f0ae1c","timestamp":"2026-03-03T07:34:36.764Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x160cb9zefcm_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"error\":\"Invalid API key.\"}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2912,"aggregated":"{\"error\":\"Invalid API key.\"}","cwd":"/Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772523276760}}
{"type":"message","id":"7f76b2fe","parentId":"5b760bd5","timestamp":"2026-03-03T07:34:43.082Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Finnhub API需要API key。QVeris应该有自己的finnhub集成。让我再看看能否找到能用的finnhub工具。\n\n实际上，我注意到之前的调用参数确实没有正确传递。这可能是QVeris的问题。\n\n让我先查看用户的需求：热度>=80的新闻。Finnhub的API返回的新闻没有热度/相关性分数，但Alpha Vantage的NEWS_SENTIMENT有。\n\n让我检查一下Alpha Vantage的API。Alpha Vantage的NEWS_SENTIMENT返回的JSON中应该有relevance_score字段。\n\n让我看看有没有其他方式可以访问Alpha Vantage API。让我使用一个正确的工具ID。","thinkingSignature":"512c4fd8db41391350e985a2a4f66fa1292d0bb01e5a17c46d29b6b7024cef50"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_umozgszau05f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && node scripts/qveris_tool.mjs search \"Alpha Vantage news sentiment relevance\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":30434,"output":184,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44602,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772523276764}}
{"type":"message","id":"73920d05","parentId":"7f76b2fe","timestamp":"2026-03-03T07:34:44.939Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_umozgszau05f_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Alpha Vantage news sentiment relevance\",\n  \"total\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.467a92c0\",\n      \"name\": \"Market News & Sentiment Trending\",\n      \"description\": \"This API returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from a large & growing selection of premier news outlets around the world, covering stocks, cryptocurrencies, forex, and a wide range of topics such as fiscal policy, mergers & acquisitions, IPOs, etc.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"function\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The function of your choice. In this case, function=NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"tickers\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The stock/crypto/forex symbols of your choice. For example: tickers=IBM will filter for articles that mention the IBM ticker; tickers=COIN,CRYPTO:BTC,FOREX:USD will filter for articles that simultaneously mention Coinbase (COIN), Bitcoin (CRYPTO:BTC), and US Dollar (FOREX:USD) in their content.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"topics\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The news topics of your choice. For example: topics=technology will filter for articles that write about the technology sector; topics=technology,ipo will filter for articles that simultaneously cover technology and IPO in their content. Below is the full list of supported topics: Blockchain: blockchain, Earnings: earnings, IPO: ipo, Mergers & Acquisitions: mergers_and_acquisitions, Financial Markets: financial_markets, Economy - Fiscal Policy (e.g., tax reform, government spending): economy_fiscal, Economy - Monetary Policy (e.g., interest rates, inflation): economy_monetary, Economy - Macro/Overall: economy_macro, Energy & Transportation: energy_transportation, Finance: finance, Life Sciences: life_sciences, Manufacturing: manufacturing, Real Estate & Construction: real_estate, Retail & Wholesale: retail_wholesale, Technology: technology.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The time range of the news articles you are targeting, in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format. For example: time_from=20220410T0130. If time_from is specified but time_to is missing, the API will return articles published between the time_from value and the current time.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The time range of the news articles you are targeting, in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"sort\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"By default, sort=LATEST and the API will return the latest articles first. You can also set sort=EARLIEST or sort=RELEVANCE based on your use case.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"LATEST\",\n            \"EARLIEST\",\n            \"RELEVANCE\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"By default, limit=50 and the API will return up to 50 matching results. You can also set limit=1000 to output up to 1000 results.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"function\": \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 883.34,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.946\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"eodhd.sentiments.retrieve.v1.c2c27d35\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Sentiment Data\",\n      \"description\": \"Get sentiment scores for one or more financial instruments (stocks, ETFs, crypto) calculated from news and social media, normalized on a scale from -1 (very negative) to 1 (very positive).\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"s\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"One or more comma-separated tickers, for example: AAPL.US,BTC-USD.CC\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Start date for filtering sentiment data (YYYY-MM-DD)\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"End date for filtering sentiment data (YYYY-MM-DD)\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"s\": \"AAPL.US,BTC-USD.CC\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Access historical end-of-day stock prices, intraday data, US stock options, and real-time prices with free and advanced plans. EODHD provides financial data for 150,000+ tickers, including stocks, ETFs, funds, and currencies worldwide.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 1278.53,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.999\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.7aca3c4a\",\n      \"name\": \"Market News & Sentiment\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from global news outlets covering stocks, crypto, forex, and economic topics.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"function\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The function to call. In this case, NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"tickers\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of stock/crypto/forex symbols to filter articles by (e.g., AAPL,CRYPTO:BTC).\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"topics\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of topics to filter by.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"blockchain\",\n            \"earnings\",\n            \"ipo\",\n            \"mergers_and_acquisitions\",\n            \"financial_markets\",\n            \"economy_fiscal\",\n            \"economy_monetary\",\n            \"economy_macro\",\n            \"energy_transportation\",\n            \"finance\",\n            \"life_sciences\",\n            \"manufacturing\",\n            \"real_estate\",\n            \"retail_wholesale\",\n            \"technology\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Start time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format (e.g., 20220410T0130).\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"End time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"sort\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Sorting method for results.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"LATEST\",\n            \"EARLIEST\",\n            \"RELEVANCE\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Maximum number of results (up to 1000).\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"function\": \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 520.43,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.987\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"alphavantage.news_sentiment.retrieve.v1.7aca3c4a\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Market News & Sentiment\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from premier news outlets around the world, covering stocks, cryptocurrencies, forex, and various financial topics.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"function\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The function name.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"tickers\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of stock/crypto/forex symbols (e.g., COIN,CRYPTO:BTC,FOREX:USD). Filters articles that mention all listed tickers.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"topics\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of topics. Articles must cover all listed topics.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"blockchain\",\n            \"earnings\",\n            \"ipo\",\n            \"mergers_and_acquisitions\",\n            \"financial_markets\",\n            \"economy_fiscal\",\n            \"economy_monetary\",\n            \"economy_macro\",\n            \"energy_transportation\",\n            \"finance\",\n            \"life_sciences\",\n            \"manufacturing\",\n            \"real_estate\",\n            \"retail_wholesale\",\n            \"technology\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Start time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format (e.g., 20220410T0130).\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"End time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"sort\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Sorting method.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"LATEST\",\n            \"EARLIEST\",\n            \"RELEVANCE\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Maximum number of results (up to 1000).\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"function\": \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 660.49,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.973\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"finnhub.stock.insidersentiment.retrieve.v1.dff02940\",\n      \"name\": \"Insider Sentiment\",\n      \"description\": \"Get insider sentiment data for US companies calculated using method discussed <a href=\\\"https://medium.com/@stock-api/finnhub-insiders-sentiment-analysis-cc43f9f64b3a\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here</a>. The MSPR ranges from -100 for the most negative to 100 for the most positive which can signal price changes in the coming 30-90 days.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"symbol\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Symbol of the company: AAPL.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"From date: 2020-03-15.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"To date: 2020-03-16.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"to\": \"2020-03-16\",\n          \"from\": \"2020-03-15\",\n          \"symbol\": \"AAPL\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Finnhub - Free APIs for realtime stock, forex, and cryptocurrency. Company fundamentals, Economic data, and Alternative data.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 3.579,\n        \"success_rate\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"eodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Financial News\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns the latest financial news headlines and full articles for a given ticker symbol or topic tag. Requires either a ticker (s) or a tag (t). Supports filtering by date, pagination, and JSON response format.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"s\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The ticker code to retrieve news for, for example: AAPL.US\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"t\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The topic tag to retrieve news for, for example: technology\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Start date for filtering news (YYYY-MM-DD)\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"End date for filtering news (YYYY-MM-DD)\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Number of results to return (default: 50, minimum: 1, maximum: 1000)\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"offset\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Offset for pagination (default: 0)\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"fmt\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Response format, either json or xml (default: json)\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {}\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Access historical end-of-day stock prices, intraday data, US stock options, and real-time prices with free and advanced plans. EODHD provides financial data for 150,000+ tickers, including stocks, ETFs, funds, and currencies worldwide.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 1.183,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.741\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"alphavantage.earnings_call_transcript.query.v1.467a92c0\",\n      \"name\": \"Earnings Call Transcript Trending\",\n      \"description\": \"This API returns the earnings call transcript for a given company in a specific quarter, covering over 15 years of history and enriched with LLM-based sentiment signals.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"function\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The function of your choice. In this case, function=EARNINGS_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"EARNINGS_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"symbol\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The symbol of the ticker of your choice. For example: symbol=IBM.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"quarter\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Fiscal quarter in YYYYQM format. For example: quarter=2024Q1. Any quarter since 2010Q1 is supported.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"symbol\": \"IBM\",\n          \"quarter\": \"2024Q1\",\n          \"function\": \"EARNINGS_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 1.507,\n        \"success_rate\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"finnhub.stock.insidersentiment.retrieve.v1.73d5f376\",\n      \"name\": \"Insider Sentiment\",\n      \"description\": \"Get insider sentiment data for US companies calculated using method discussed <a href=\\\"https://medium.com/@stock-api/finnhub-insiders-sentiment-analysis-cc43f9f64b3a\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here</a>. The MSPR ranges from -100 for the most negative to 100 for the most positive which can signal price changes in the coming 30-90 days.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"symbol\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Symbol of the company: AAPL.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"From date: 2020-03-15.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"To date: 2020-03-16.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"to\": \"2020-03-16\",\n          \"from\": \"2020-03-15\",\n          \"symbol\": \"AAPL\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Finnhub - Free APIs for realtime stock, forex, and cryptocurrency. Company fundamentals, Economic data, and Alternative data.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 2.553,\n        \"success_rate\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"finnhub.stock.insidersentiment.retrieve.v1\",\n      \"name\": \"Insider Sentiment\",\n      \"description\": \"Get insider sentiment data for US companies calculated using method discussed <a href=\\\"https://medium.com/@stock-api/finnhub-insiders-sentiment-analysis-cc43f9f64b3a\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">here</a>. The MSPR ranges from -100 for the most negative to 100 for the most positive which can signal price changes in the coming 30-90 days.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"symbol\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Symbol of the company: AAPL.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"From date: 2020-03-15.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"To date: 2020-03-16.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"to\": \"2020-03-16\",\n          \"from\": \"2020-03-15\",\n          \"symbol\": \"AAPL\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Finnhub - Free APIs for realtime stock, forex, and cryptocurrency. Company fundamentals, Economic data, and Alternative data.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 0,\n        \"success_rate\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"alternative_crypto_fear_greed_index.fear_greed_index.retrieve.v1.fb14b8ee\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Crypto Fear & Greed Index\",\n      \"description\": \"Fetch the current or historical Crypto Fear & Greed Index values from Alternative.me.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Limit the number of returned results. Default is '1'. Use '0' for all available data. The field 'time_until_update' is only returned when limit=1.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"format\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Response format: 'json' (default) or 'csv'.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"json\",\n            \"csv\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"date_format\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Date format for timestamps: 'us' (MM/DD/YYYY), 'cn' or 'kr' (YYYY/MM/DD), 'world' (DD/MM/YYYY). Default is Unix timestamp unless format=csv, in which case default is 'world'.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"us\",\n            \"cn\",\n            \"kr\",\n            \"world\"\n          ]\n        }\n      ],\n      \"provider_description\": \"Provides a sentiment index for the Bitcoin and crypto market ranging from 0 (Extreme Fear) to 100 (Extreme Greed).\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 1187.9,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.999\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"search_id\": \"136ba5c5-085b-400f-9038-35f2e8d4c612\",\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 539.01\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1852,"aggregated":"{\n  \"query\": \"Alpha Vantage news sentiment relevance\",\n  \"total\": 10,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.467a92c0\",\n      \"name\": \"Market News & Sentiment Trending\",\n      \"description\": \"This API returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from a large & growing selection of premier news outlets around the world, covering stocks, cryptocurrencies, forex, and a wide range of topics such as fiscal policy, mergers & acquisitions, IPOs, etc.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"function\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The function of your choice. In this case, function=NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"tickers\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The stock/crypto/forex symbols of your choice. For example: tickers=IBM will filter for articles that mention the IBM ticker; tickers=COIN,CRYPTO:BTC,FOREX:USD will filter for articles that simultaneously mention Coinbase (COIN), Bitcoin (CRYPTO:BTC), and US Dollar (FOREX:USD) in their content.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"topics\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The news topics of your choice. For example: topics=technology will filter for articles that write about the technology sector; topics=technology,ipo will filter for articles that simultaneously cover technology and IPO in their content. Below is the full list of supported topics: Blockchain: blockchain, Earnings: earnings, IPO: ipo, Mergers & Acquisitions: mergers_and_acquisitions, Financial Markets: financial_markets, Economy - Fiscal Policy (e.g., tax reform, government spending): economy_fiscal, Economy - Monetary Policy (e.g., interest rates, inflation): economy_monetary, Economy - Macro/Overall: economy_macro, Energy & Transportation: energy_transportation, Finance: finance, Life Sciences: life_sciences, Manufacturing: manufacturing, Real Estate & Construction: real_estate, Retail & Wholesale: retail_wholesale, Technology: technology.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The time range of the news articles you are targeting, in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format. For example: time_from=20220410T0130. If time_from is specified but time_to is missing, the API will return articles published between the time_from value and the current time.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The time range of the news articles you are targeting, in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"sort\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"By default, sort=LATEST and the API will return the latest articles first. You can also set sort=EARLIEST or sort=RELEVANCE based on your use case.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"LATEST\",\n            \"EARLIEST\",\n            \"RELEVANCE\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"By default, limit=50 and the API will return up to 50 matching results. You can also set limit=1000 to output up to 1000 results.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"function\": \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 883.34,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.946\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"eodhd.sentiments.retrieve.v1.c2c27d35\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Sentiment Data\",\n      \"description\": \"Get sentiment scores for one or more financial instruments (stocks, ETFs, crypto) calculated from news and social media, normalized on a scale from -1 (very negative) to 1 (very positive).\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"s\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"One or more comma-separated tickers, for example: AAPL.US,BTC-USD.CC\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Start date for filtering sentiment data (YYYY-MM-DD)\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"End date for filtering sentiment data (YYYY-MM-DD)\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"s\": \"AAPL.US,BTC-USD.CC\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Access historical end-of-day stock prices, intraday data, US stock options, and real-time prices with free and advanced plans. EODHD provides financial data for 150,000+ tickers, including stocks, ETFs, funds, and currencies worldwide.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 1278.53,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.999\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"alphavantage.news_sentiment.query.v1.7aca3c4a\",\n      \"name\": \"Market News & Sentiment\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from global news outlets covering stocks, crypto, forex, and economic topics.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"function\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The function to call. In this case, NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"tickers\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of stock/crypto/forex symbols to filter articles by (e.g., AAPL,CRYPTO:BTC).\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"topics\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of topics to filter by.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"blockchain\",\n            \"earnings\",\n            \"ipo\",\n            \"mergers_and_acquisitions\",\n            \"financial_markets\",\n            \"economy_fiscal\",\n            \"economy_monetary\",\n            \"economy_macro\",\n            \"energy_transportation\",\n            \"finance\",\n            \"life_sciences\",\n            \"manufacturing\",\n            \"real_estate\",\n            \"retail_wholesale\",\n            \"technology\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_from\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Start time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format (e.g., 20220410T0130).\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"time_to\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"End time in YYYYMMDDTHHMM format.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"sort\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Sorting method for results.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"LATEST\",\n            \"EARLIEST\",\n            \"RELEVANCE\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"limit\",\n          \"type\": \"integer\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Maximum number of results (up to 1000).\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"examples\": {\n        \"sample_parameters\": {\n          \"function\": \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"provider_description\": \"Alpha Vantage provides realtime and historical financial market data through a set of powerful and developer-friendly data APIs and spreadsheets. From traditional asset classes (e.g., stocks, ETFs, mutual funds) to economic indicators, from foreign exchange rates to commodities, from fundamental data to technical indicators, Alpha Vantage is your one-stop-shop for enterprise-grade global market data delivered through cloud-based APIs, MCP servers, spreadsheets, and more.\",\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"avg_execution_time_ms\": 520.43,\n        \"success_rate\": 0.987\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"tool_id\": \"alphavantage.news_sentiment.retrieve.v1.7aca3c4a\",\n      \"name\": \"Retrieve Market News & Sentiment\",\n      \"description\": \"Returns live and historical market news & sentiment data from premier news outlets around the world, covering stocks, cryptocurrencies, forex, and various financial topics.\",\n      \"params\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"function\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": true,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"The function name.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"NEWS_SENTIMENT\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"tickers\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of stock/crypto/forex symbols (e.g., COIN,CRYPTO:BTC,FOREX:USD). Filters articles that mention all listed tickers.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"topics\",\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"required\": false,\n          \"description\": {\n            \"en\": \"Comma-separated list of topics. Articles must cover all listed topics.\"\n          },\n          \"enum\": [\n            \"blockchain\",\n            \"earnings\",\n            \"ipo\",\n            \"mergers_and_acquisitions\",\n            \"financial_markets\",\n            \"economy_fiscal\",\n            \"economy_monetary\",\n            \"economy_macro\",\n            \"energy_transportation\",\n            \"finance\",\n        